sql:
SELECT year, dow_performance
FROM investment_performance
WHERE economic_growth > 2;

SELECT DISTINCT year
FROM investment_performance
ORDER BY year;

SELECT quarterly_performance
FROM investment_returns
WHERE investment_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "Blooming years" refers to years where investment performance exceeds the average;
- "Flourishing investment types" are categories of investment that experience significant growth;
- "Thriving financial indices" are benchmarks that showcase above-average performance;
- "Seeds of success are sown more than once" means that there are multiple records of successful performance within a year, type, and index combination.

sql:
SELECT AVG(average_performance) AS overall_average_performance
FROM (
    SELECT AVG(performance) AS average_performance
    FROM investment_returns
    GROUP BY type_id
) AS subquery;

SELECT MAX(inflation_rate) 
FROM investment_performance 
WHERE economic_growth < 0;

SELECT category_id, ACOS(performance) AS radian_performance
FROM investment_returns
ORDER BY radian_performance DESC;

SELECT year, dow_performance
FROM investment_performance
ORDER BY dow_performance DESC;

SELECT index_name, index_description
FROM financial_indices
WHERE benchmark = 0;

SELECT AVG(average_return) AS average_medium_risk_return
FROM investment_types
WHERE risk_level = 'medium';

external_knowledge:
- Growth rate calculation: (Current performance - Previous performance) / Previous performance;
- Dow Jones performance represents the market's health, akin to a voyage's journey markers;
- Users and investment categories are metaphorically described as voyagers and compasses, respectively;
- The transformation of the market, represented by the growth rate, symbolizes the winds of change impacting the journey.
